{"sequence":55,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T08:40:54.008587565Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-143a7e7b","body":"finding_summary: The new milestone-bundle contract is still only enforced by prompt text; domain validation continues to accept underspecified bead proposals and legacy one-way AC mappings.\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs\n- src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs\nevidence:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:141-145 only rejects an empty `title`; there is still no check that each bead has the newly required `description`, `bead_type`, `priority`, or non-empty `labels`, and no range check that `priority` stays within the new 1..=3 guidance.\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:1099-1106 still silently backfills empty `acceptance_map[].covered_by`, so a planner output that omits the bidirectional mapping entirely is treated as valid.\n- src/contexts/requirements_drafting/contracts.rs:372-377 accepts any milestone bundle that passes `p.validate()`, so these omissions still make it all the way through the pipeline.\nremediation_hint: Tighten milestone-bundle validation for newly generated outputs so bead descriptions/type/priority/labels are required, priority is constrained to the supported values, and `acceptance_map[].covered_by` must be explicitly present instead of relying on legacy backfill.","dedup_key":"792dbc1218df44ce951ceee1f3378da4ba1abe2e2d4a4746413f908f831a8c7e","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417072108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":56,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T08:40:54.018043473Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-387ce418","body":"finding_summary: The prompt now asks for `depends_on` and `covered_by` bead IDs, but it never tells the model to assign a stable `bead_id` to each bead proposal.\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/workspace_governance/template_catalog.rs\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs\nevidence:\n- src/contexts/workspace_governance/template_catalog.rs:337-349 describes titles, descriptions, priorities, labels, dependencies, and AC coverage, but there is no instruction to emit a `bead_id` per bead.\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:1052-1065 only synthesizes implicit `bead-N` identifiers after parsing, so an LLM response without explicit IDs has to guess hidden slot numbers to make `depends_on` / `covered_by` line up.\nremediation_hint: Update the milestone-bundle template to require a stable `bead_id` on every bead proposal and to reuse those same IDs everywhere cross-references appear.","dedup_key":"9ef221300888c4c4c2fe728afdc9daa5a1487d6deb72f3a59bf0bf84ef9b93c5","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417072108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":57,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T08:40:54.027024269Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-d31a05b7","body":"finding_summary: `validate_dependency_graph()` does not reliably report graph problems on partially invalid bundles, because it is layered on top of full bundle validation and graph analysis is skipped once any earlier error exists.\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs\nevidence:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:963-965 implements `validate_dependency_graph()` by calling `validated_canonical_bundle()`.\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:1041-1043 shows `validated_canonical_bundle()` calling `bundle.validate()` first.\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:273-325 only invokes `dependency_graph_analysis_from_canonical()` inside `if errors.is_empty()`, so an unrelated metadata or AC error suppresses the cycle / missing-target diagnostics that this helper is supposed to surface.\nremediation_hint: Make `validate_dependency_graph()` canonicalize references and run graph checks independently, or have it return graph diagnostics alongside non-graph validation failures.","dedup_key":"d6462bb20c1b4c0c4c611190aeac4c6d04e5bc3b848ef95ead55c134ce929b09","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417072108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
