{"sequence":76,"timestamp":"2026-04-17T09:14:51.882660479Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-76d8edde","body":"finding_summary: `MilestoneBundle::validate()` is now backwards-incompatible with previously accepted milestone payloads. The new hard requirements for bead `description`, `bead_type`, `priority`, `labels`, and non-empty `acceptance_map.covered_by` at `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:146`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:155`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:164`, `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:171`, and `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:279`, combined with `canonicalize_bundle()` no longer rebuilding empty `covered_by` entries in `src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs:1155`, mean older planner payloads now deserialize successfully but fail runtime validation. That breaks real workflows because completed requirements runs persist the raw planner bundle at `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:1829` and revalidate it during handoff at `src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs:2358`, so an already-completed run can become impossible to hand off or materialize after upgrade.\naffected_files:\n- src/contexts/milestone_record/bundle.rs\n- src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs\nremediation_hint: Keep the stricter prompt guidance, but preserve legacy compatibility by backfilling missing `covered_by` and tolerating absent legacy bead metadata during load/canonicalization, or add an explicit migration path before `validate()` rejects older bundles.","dedup_key":"6c2fe1dae79132d301a67dcf93a34247b3d55e34a7c3cbbbcdb2573f91877980","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260417072108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
